cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper deals with weakly supervised learning for facial behavior analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of graphical models and high-order potentials, which are also common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of video sequences, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
